What you need to know:

Commonwealth Secretary General Patricia Scotland named Wafula -Strike to that role in December 2020 and the Paralympian has taken to her job with gusto championing accessibility and inclusivity for all."Everyone has the right to access the opportunities that sport, and physical activity offers. Participation in sport and physical activity is important in promoting inclusion right across society. Individuals and groups that are excluded or marginalised in sport have limited voice and power to affect the attitudes, norms, policies, and practices that created social exclusion in sport in the first place," she said.